comment_text: "Pour ceux qui se demandent ce que signifie le nom ""Mistral Gagnant"", voici une petite explication: Mistral Gagnant"" √©tait le nom d'une poudre vendue dans un sachet herm√©tique dans lequel on pouvait verser de l'eau, et cela faisait un soda orange ou citron. Et il s'appelait ""Gagnant"", parce qu'en retournant le sachet, on pouvait lire dans certains cas la mention ""Gagnant"", ce qui permettait d'en avoir un gratuit en rapportant le papier au marchand.  Renaud, trente ans plus tard, prom√®ne sa fillette de 3 ou 4 ans, et repense du coup √† son enfance, alors il veut lui faire d√©couvrir les bonbons qu'il aimait √©tant enfant: Les caramels √† un franc(ancien franc des ann√©es 50), les Coco Bohair, vendus dans une petite poche m√©tallique avec laquelle on se coupait la langue les jours de maladresse, et les Mistral Gagnant: En promenant sa fille, Renaud se rend compte que tous ces bonbons ont disparu: Il voudrait les lui faire d√©couvrir, on devine qu'il a cherch√© dans les magasins, mais les commer√ßants lui expliquent ce ""√ßa ne se fait plus""... D'o√π la fin: ""Le temps est assassin et emporte avec lui les rires des enfants... et les Mistral Gagnant"". Renaud, d√©sabus√©, a perdu son rire d'enfant, et il ne retrouvera plus les saveurs de son enfance, mais il veut malgr√© tout continuer √† aimer la vie. C'est une histoire tr√®s simple, mais sublime, parfaitement racont√©e, sur une musique magique qui exhale toute la puret√© de l'enfance. S'il n'y avait qu'un disque de chansons pour le monde entier, ""Mistral Gagnant"" y aurait s√ªrement sa place."

author: wongawonga1000
comment_text: The smug attitude shown by some of the team members was totally uncalled for. Most people who start driving these cars have been racing from a very young age and so have time to build the skill level required to handle a high performance vehicle. Richard is a TV show host who's probably never done any serious racing in his life - especially at that level. It's little wonder then that he had trouble driving the cars and was constantly stalling them. Even Lewis Hamilton, who appeared immediately after this segment, said that those cars were very difficult to drive. In this situation therefore, a little understanding wouldn't have gone astray - particularly given the steep learning curve Richard was faced with.

author: tin long yuen
comment_text: Well.. it is too hard for me choice one from them.... Therefore, i brought both the ST and RS 220, haha. But i have to said that the Fiesta is simply much more fun to drive which the RS can't give you on the street. The sharpness and responsiveness of the Fiesta is amazing. On top of that, you wont be feeling any turbo lag on the fiesta at all. Unlike the RS 220, there is a window that you have to wait for the boost to come around 1k rpm to 2k rpm. This is really the biggest different.   However, the RS is just quicker. (I put MP215 to mine as well), it gives you the stability in high speed and also in the corner which the Fiesta can't offer. (i put F1A3 in Fiesta and PSS in RS).

author: anthony perkins
comment_text: The LR Discovery Series II was never tested for safety by EURONCAP and was merely a facelift and cosmetic changes to the original LR Discovery Series I.   The old design was made before safety was even thought of and wouldn't keep anyone safe in a collision.  All the Disco I and Disco II got were driver airbags at first followed by twin driver / passenger airbags as standard but apart from this no real changes to the design for safety in a collision.  The Renault Espace is the far safer place to be and people would be far less injured in it, than the Discovery.

author: Paolo Ciarpaglini
comment_text: "X Roberto ... Oggi ci sono i bimbiminchia come li chiami tu, ai nostri tempi c'erano i bimbipiloti. Insomma i tempi sono mutati e a nassuno interessa piu' affiancarsi al semaforo e ... via. Il problema e' almeno per me che faccio molta fatica ad abituarmi a una realta' mutata tutta a favore di loro, e mi mancano tanto, da morire le serate dei fine settimana in cui mi sentivo il re del mondo. Cio' che resta sono ricordi di un tempo che sembra impossibile essere esistito, che faceva coppia perfetta con i ""nativi"", i veri e unici abitanti di quelle sere. Mi vestivo scendevo e al momento di accenderla iniziava una sorta di danza e istinto tribale, fatto di rumori e suoni che esprimevano piccoli sogni divenuti reali. Erano tempi infinitamente piu' a misura d'uomo, di esseri umani che trascorsa l'infanzia in canottiera bianca e appena uscita dalla disco '80, si affacciava verso l'ultimo decennio sulle note di ""Cosa restera'"" di Raf e la PX elaborata ancora in garage. Con l'avvento dei duemila e' iniziata una mutazione genetica divenuta poi sempre piu' frenetica, folle, un no sense mentre i capelli bianchi aumentavano e iniziavi (parlo per me) a sentirti come un orologio fuori sincronia. Continuo ad osservare tutto cio' e ancora non mi capacito di cosa e' accaduto, ai prati dove giocavamo e a regole non scritte che facevano di quei tempi qualcosa di molto migliore, di semplice, di indimenticabile. Salutai la mia Uno prima serie nel '98 e fu come staccarmi qualcosa che sapevo non avrei mai piu' avuto. Ma .. The show must go on e il destino ha voluto che due anni fa acquistassi una Punto 2^ serie hgt nera tenuta benissimo che mi aiuta a sentirmi meno sperduto in mezzo a tutte queste auto tutte uguali computerizzate, avanzate ma che non sanno neppure di acqua calda. Qualcuno mi guarda ogni tanto quasi fossi un marziano, ma faccio finta di niente. Dimenticavo ""la bara"", soli 149 cv alla ruota con turbina originale e pressione di sicurezza ad 1 bar, piu' un profondo lavoro che mi costo' 9 milioni e ottocento mila lire. Non capisco il volerne 220 poiche' ingestibili e fatti per durare appena il tempo della spesa. Non so se hai notato ma fumano entrambe in modo poco incoraggiante. E poi 245 di tachimetro erano piu' che sufficenti. Come i miei 30 anni trascorsi ormai da un pezzo, anzi un era. Ma .. e' la vita."

author: KerberosRS
comment_text: "Oggi ho 45 anni e io avevo una Fiesta Turbo 133cv ( quella con le strisce verdi per chi si ricorda), diretta concorrente di questi mostri. Sebbene molti dicono lo fosse anche la mia per me queste auto non erano delle bare la mia ce l'ho avuta per 5 anni e no ho mai fatto un graffio ( come nei restanti anni di guida d'altronde).... per√≤ se posso dire la mia esperienza devo ammettere che il sistema di frenata di queste auto era assolutamente inadeguato... il fatto di non avere un ABS portava all inevitabile blocco dei pneumatici anteriori nelle frenate di emergenza ed era facile "" andare dritto""..io ricordo che per ovviare il problema facevo manualmente l'effetto dell'ABS prima spingendo con decisione e appena avvertivo il blocco dei pneumatici saltellando con decisione con la pianta del piede sul freno. Comunque questi motori erano davvero pazzeschi a volte la turbina dava dei contraccolpi tali che si facevano veri e propri salti sui sedili ( per fortuna avevo dei fantastici RECARO). Ricordo che quando l'ho demolita nel 2002 piansi per una mezz'ora buona come se fosse morta una persona a me cara....ancora oggi ogni tanto vado a cercare le vecchie foto ( su carta stampata e poi digitalizzate) fatte con lei..ricordi.. di gioie... dolori ...vacanze....spensieratezza..follia ... amiche e vecchi amici."

author: aditya giri
comment_text: I purchased Renault Kwid Rxt model in March 2017 from Avia Auto Services Patpadganj branch. Since then in less than a year I have taken my car to service station for over 10 times for various issues.  Issue No. 1 When I purchased the car I was fraudulently given a Comprehensive Insurance Policy instead of a Zero Dep. Policy. Which incurred me losses every time I claimed my insurance.  Issue No.2 There is only one reverse light in the car on the left side and no light is provided at the right side of vehicle which creates problem whenever I try to reverse my car.  Issue No. 3 They claim that car gives an average of 25kmpl. Which I totally false claim and nowhere near 25 kmpl you can expect in a city like Delhi.  Issue No. 4 Back in July 2017 when monsoon begun, my car got flooded with rain water and my laptop and documents were destroyed.   Issue No.5 The body is made of plastic and is so is the base of engine. The engine due to a small stone got damaged and oil chambers had to change. Which costed me 7500 approx. The service department asked me to get an engine protection for Rs 1800/- which the Renault was supposed to install before selling the vehicle.  Issue 6 Since I was not holding a zero dep policy in the first year I faced great difficulty in purchasing a zero dep this year. The Renault Team is so unprofessional that they don't even reply to my mails and complaints.   If you are planning to buy Renault car kindly have a review from it's prior users and watch YouTube videos regarding issues with Renault car. I have been duped but I want to beware other innocent buyers from buying this piece of plastic.   If you are also suffering from same kindly contact me at: giriaditya5@yahoo.co.in  Since I am planning to move to consumer court soon for this harassment, cheating & fraud.

author: Don Jonson
comment_text: Nice... but, I'll still rather have my 1976 lincoln town car. 7.8 liter engine (460) 4 barrel carb. It had the trailer pulling package so that included 4 wheel disc brakes, a 3 core radiator, and posi-traction rear end. It weighed, about 5500 lbs. The hood itself is like 6 feet long. LOTS of room for impact and lots of material to absorb a crash.  Yeah, so it got 9 mpg. It was comfy, good in the winter (you would be surprised how good because of the posi and the weight), and safe.   Shit, I could fit that whole Renault in my hood.   I was rear-ended in it back in 1984 by some jerk in a Chevy Monza.  He hit me doing about 25 mph. My big heavy chrome bumper was bent a little but no damage to the trunk.  meanwhile, his 2 front quarter panels were pushed over his doors. . he cold not open his door and had to crawl out the window. Wheels bent, front glass broken and every fluid in the car was leaking out the bottom. His car was un-driveable.  My friends and I felt a small BUMP when he hit us.   His car was towed and totaled. I drove away and for $900 my car was repaired.

author: Ishan Ghai
comment_text: Renault KWID caught Fire  Renault India for supplying me faulty vehicle Renault Kwid RXT model purchased on 26/10/15 with no extra fittings/ accessories except mud flaps.After my first summer trip to faridabad, came back home around 5pm, thereafter it was a nightmare for us, as around 12 mid night, we woked up by alarms from neighbours of fire in our car. We poured water to extinguish the fire. On inspection of car we observed the engine compartment fully melted down due to internal wiring / faulty design, in parked conditions. We came to know of damage, only when car catched fire around 12 mid night. We thank our stars, that this top end model didn't catches fire, when we were driving the car. Renault India cheated on us, by introducing unsafe car in India. A Complaint was lodged with Renault at 1 AM after the incidence. In morning, on Complaint to Renault 24 hour help line, my car was picked up and inspected. The car engine was fully gutted, even tyres were got affected. I was told we would be given a new car as replacement as car has been damaged due to fault in design /wiring. All Renault staff asked us many questions and even visited the site of incidence. A Complaint no. 4-01783350 dated 11/4/16 was lodged with Renault customer care. To surprise we received a call from Mr. Gaurav Negi, Renault India on 13/4/16 followed by letter from Ms. Neetu Chawla, Renault India informing us that the car technology is tamper proof. We doused the fire ourself, without informing Delhi Fire Brigade & Delhi Police and disconnected battery terminal to prevent further burning due to short circuit & petrol tank catching fire We are elderly senior citizen couple living in Delhi, with both sons staying in Germany. We are very worried to see the fire in engine. We fear risk to our life. We purchased this car from our savings. Renault India is deliberately denying their faulty design as reason for fire in engine. The car has run less than 2000 km in five months. The Renault Kwid has 2 years warranty against manufacturing defects as per the clause 2 of Terms and Conditions of KWID Vehicle WarrantY They have kept our car at their workshop at Rama Road, Delhi since early morning 11/4/16 with no action taken to provide us alternate car for usage till time new car is provided to us as replacement. Please take action against Renault India and direct them to stop sales of their defective designed car KWID in market, till period the defect is removed and they declare their KWID is safe to drive, in Indian condition. I request you to direct Delhi Fire Brigade and Delhi Police to take suo motto cognizance of fire in Renault Kwid Car engine and take action to stop sales of KWID in Indian market. Sincerely, Rajesh Ghai B6/70 sector 8, Rohini, Delhi-110085 9810434027 : 01147541414 .

comment_text: "Pour ceux qui se demandent ce que signifie le nom ""Mistral Gagnant"", voici une petite explication: Mistral Gagnant"" √©tait le nom d'une poudre vendue dans un sachet herm√©tique dans lequel on pouvait verser de l'eau, et cela faisait un soda orange ou citron. Et il s'appelait ""Gagnant"", parce qu'en retournant le sachet, on pouvait lire dans certains cas la mention ""Gagnant"", ce qui permettait d'en avoir un gratuit en rapportant le papier au marchand.  Renaud, trente ans plus tard, prom√®ne sa fillette de 3 ou 4 ans, et repense du coup √† son enfance, alors il veut lui faire d√©couvrir les bonbons qu'il aimait √©tant enfant: Les caramels √† un franc(ancien franc des ann√©es 50), les Coco Bohair, vendus dans une petite poche m√©tallique avec laquelle on se coupait la langue les jours de maladresse, et les Mistral Gagnant: En promenant sa fille, Renaud se rend compte que tous ces bonbons ont disparu: Il voudrait les lui faire d√©couvrir, on devine qu'il a cherch√© dans les magasins, mais les commer√ßants lui expliquent ce ""√ßa ne se fait plus""... S'il n'y avait qu'un disque de chansons pour le monde entier, ""Mistral Gagnant"" y aurait s√ªrement sa place."

author: wongawonga1000
comment_text: The smug attitude shown by some of the team members was totally uncalled for. Most people who start driving these cars have been racing from a very young age and so have time to build the skill level required to handle a high performance vehicle. Richard is a TV show host who's probably never done any serious racing in his life - especially at that level. It's little wonder then that he had trouble driving the cars and was constantly stalling them. Even Lewis Hamilton, who appeared immediately after this segment, said that those cars were very difficult to drive. In this situation therefore, a little understanding wouldn't have gone astray - particularly given the steep learning curve Richard was faced with.

author: Wayne Rhodes
comment_text: With nothing more than 93 octane and pulled the rubber seal out of the intake track so she gets fresh outside air and a 15 0z. bottle of Lucas octane booster, shifting without lifting, she gets to 60 in just a tick over 6 seconds in sport mod, and it really made this little light weight come alive took out the full size spare tire 37 pounds of weight savings I carry an electric air pump and a can of fix-a-flat with me at all times. If I did not have to shift to third it would get to 60 in just under 6 seconds I am sure of it. It now has almost 4000 miles on its clock and two oil changes already one at 500 miles and the other at 2000 miles. I could not be happier than I am right now with my new Fiesta St. As Harris would say I really have to think on this but the Ford is simply brilliant, she corners flat you can't put a price on this.

comment_text: Well.. it is too hard for me choice one from them.... Therefore, i brought both the ST and RS 220, haha. But i have to said that the Fiesta is simply much more fun to drive which the RS can't give you on the street. The sharpness and responsiveness of the Fiesta is amazing. On top of that, you wont be feeling any turbo lag on the fiesta at all. Unlike the RS 220, there is a window that you have to wait for the boost to come around 1k rpm to 2k rpm. This is really the biggest different.   However, the RS is just quicker. (I put MP215 to mine as well), it gives you the stability in high speed and also in the corner which the Fiesta can't offer. (i put F1A3 in Fiesta and PSS in RS).

author: anthony perkins
comment_text: The LR Discovery Series II was never tested for safety by EURONCAP and was merely a facelift and cosmetic changes to the original LR Discovery Series I.   The old design was made before safety was even thought of and wouldn't keep anyone safe in a collision.  All the Disco I and Disco II got were driver airbags at first followed by twin driver / passenger airbags as standard but apart from this no real changes to the design for safety in a collision.  The Renault Espace is the far safer place to be and people would be far less injured in it, than the Discovery.

comment_text: "There are ""no chase"" policies in many places for a reason. Chasing this motorcycle is only increasing the threat to people's lives. He crashes that motorcycle, he dies. Police crash that car and the likelihood of someone else dying goes up exponentially. Especially when the bike has something to run from now, pushing his speed from 230km/hr to 299+km/hr. It's just not worth chasing speeders that are going that fast unless they have committed some kind of violent crime before running at that speed. The likelyhood of a negative outcome is very high when a hypercar is chasing a sportbike down the road at 300km/hr in a non closed environment. The very premise of this video is rather unintelligent."

author: Paolo Ciarpaglini
comment_text: "X Roberto ... Oggi ci sono i bimbiminchia come li chiami tu, ai nostri tempi c'erano i bimbipiloti. Insomma i tempi sono mutati e a nassuno interessa piu' affiancarsi al semaforo e ... via. Il problema e' almeno per me che faccio molta fatica ad abituarmi a una realta' mutata tutta a favore di loro, e mi mancano tanto, da morire le serate dei fine settimana in cui mi sentivo il re del mondo. Cio' che resta sono ricordi di un tempo che sembra impossibile essere esistito, che faceva coppia perfetta con i ""nativi"", i veri e unici abitanti di quelle sere. Mi vestivo scendevo e al momento di accenderla iniziava una sorta di danza e istinto tribale, fatto di rumori e suoni che esprimevano piccoli sogni divenuti reali. Erano tempi infinitamente piu' a misura d'uomo, di esseri umani che trascorsa l'infanzia in canottiera bianca e appena uscita dalla disco '80, si affacciava verso l'ultimo decennio sulle note di ""Cosa restera'"" di Raf e la PX elaborata ancora in garage. Con l'avvento dei duemila e' iniziata una mutazione genetica divenuta poi sempre piu' frenetica, folle, un no sense mentre i capelli bianchi aumentavano e iniziavi (parlo per me) a sentirti come un orologio fuori sincronia. Continuo ad osservare tutto cio' e ancora non mi capacito di cosa e' accaduto, ai prati dove giocavamo e a regole non scritte che facevano di quei tempi qualcosa di molto migliore, di semplice, di indimenticabile. Salutai la mia Uno prima serie nel '98 e fu come staccarmi qualcosa che sapevo non avrei mai piu' avuto. Ma .. The show must go on e il destino ha voluto che due anni fa acquistassi una Punto 2^ serie hgt nera tenuta benissimo che mi aiuta a sentirmi meno sperduto in mezzo a tutte queste auto tutte uguali computerizzate, avanzate ma che non sanno neppure di acqua calda. Qualcuno mi guarda ogni tanto quasi fossi un marziano, ma faccio finta di niente. Dimenticavo ""la bara"", soli 149 cv alla ruota con turbina originale e pressione di sicurezza ad 1 bar, piu' un profondo lavoro che mi costo' 9 milioni e ottocento mila lire. Non capisco il volerne 220 poiche' ingestibili e fatti per durare appena il tempo della spesa. Non so se hai notato ma fumano entrambe in modo poco incoraggiante. E poi 245 di tachimetro erano piu' che sufficenti. Come i miei 30 anni trascorsi ormai da un pezzo, anzi un era. Ma .. e' la vita."

comment_text: "Oggi ho 45 anni e io avevo una Fiesta Turbo 133cv ( quella con le strisce verdi per chi si ricorda), diretta concorrente di questi mostri. Sebbene molti dicono lo fosse anche la mia per me queste auto non erano delle bare la mia ce l'ho avuta per 5 anni e no ho mai fatto un graffio ( come nei restanti anni di guida d'altronde).... per√≤ se posso dire la mia esperienza devo ammettere che il sistema di frenata di queste auto era assolutamente inadeguato... il fatto di non avere un ABS portava all inevitabile blocco dei pneumatici anteriori nelle frenate di emergenza ed era facile "" andare dritto""..io ricordo che per ovviare il problema facevo manualmente l'effetto dell'ABS prima spingendo con decisione e appena avvertivo il blocco dei pneumatici saltellando con decisione con la pianta del piede sul freno. Comunque questi motori erano davvero pazzeschi a volte la turbina dava dei contraccolpi tali che si facevano veri e propri salti sui sedili ( per fortuna avevo dei fantastici RECARO). Ricordo che quando l'ho demolita nel 2002 piansi per una mezz'ora buona come se fosse morta una persona a me cara....ancora oggi ogni tanto vado a cercare le vecchie foto ( su carta stampata e poi digitalizzate) fatte con lei..ricordi.. di gioie... dolori ...vacanze....spensieratezza..follia ... amiche e vecchi amici."

author: aditya giri
comment_text: I purchased Renault Kwid Rxt model in March 2017 from Avia Auto Services Patpadganj branch. Since then in less than a year I have taken my car to service station for over 10 times for various issues.  Issue No. 1 When I purchased the car I was fraudulently given a Comprehensive Insurance Policy instead of a Zero Dep. Policy. Which incurred me losses every time I claimed my insurance.  Issue No.2 There is only one reverse light in the car on the left side and no light is provided at the right side of vehicle which creates problem whenever I try to reverse my car.  Issue No. 3 They claim that car gives an average of 25kmpl. Which I totally false claim and nowhere near 25 kmpl you can expect in a city like Delhi.  Issue No. 4 Back in July 2017 when monsoon begun, my car got flooded with rain water and my laptop and documents were destroyed.   Issue No.5 The body is made of plastic and is so is the base of engine. The engine due to a small stone got damaged and oil chambers had to change. Which costed me 7500 approx. The service department asked me to get an engine protection for Rs 1800/- which the Renault was supposed to install before selling the vehicle.  Issue 6 Since I was not holding a zero dep policy in the first year I faced great difficulty in purchasing a zero dep this year. The Renault Team is so unprofessional that they don't even reply to my mails and complaints.   If you are planning to buy Renault car kindly have a review from it's prior users and watch YouTube videos regarding issues with Renault car. I have been duped but I want to beware other innocent buyers from buying this piece of plastic.   If you are also suffering from same kindly contact me at: giriaditya5@yahoo.co.in  Since I am planning to move to consumer court soon for this harassment, cheating & fraud.

author: Don Jonson
comment_text: Nice... but, I'll still rather have my 1976 lincoln town car. 7.8 liter engine (460) 4 barrel carb. It had the trailer pulling package so that included 4 wheel disc brakes, a 3 core radiator, and posi-traction rear end. It weighed, about 5500 lbs. The hood itself is like 6 feet long. LOTS of room for impact and lots of material to absorb a crash.  Yeah, so it got 9 mpg. It was comfy, good in the winter (you would be surprised how good because of the posi and the weight), and safe.   Shit, I could fit that whole Renault in my hood.   I was rear-ended in it back in 1984 by some jerk in a Chevy Monza.  He hit me doing about 25 mph. My big heavy chrome bumper was bent a little but no damage to the trunk.  meanwhile, his 2 front quarter panels were pushed over his doors. . he cold not open his door and had to crawl out the window. Wheels bent, front glass broken and every fluid in the car was leaking out the bottom. His car was un-driveable.  My friends and I felt a small BUMP when he hit us.   His car was towed and totaled. I drove away and for $900 my car was repaired.

author: Ishan Ghai
comment_text: Renault KWID caught Fire  Renault India for supplying me faulty vehicle Renault Kwid RXT model purchased on 26/10/15 with no extra fittings/ accessories except mud flaps.After my first summer trip to faridabad, came back home around 5pm, thereafter it was a nightmare for us, as around 12 mid night, we woked up by alarms from neighbours of fire in our car. We poured water to extinguish the fire. On inspection of car we observed the engine compartment fully melted down due to internal wiring / faulty design, in parked conditions. We came to know of damage, only when car catched fire around 12 mid night. We thank our stars, that this top end model didn't catches fire, when we were driving the car. Renault India cheated on us, by introducing unsafe car in India. A Complaint was lodged with Renault at 1 AM after the incidence. In morning, on Complaint to Renault 24 hour help line, my car was picked up and inspected. The car engine was fully gutted, even tyres were got affected. I was told we would be given a new car as replacement as car has been damaged due to fault in design /wiring. All Renault staff asked us many questions and even visited the site of incidence. A Complaint no. 4-01783350 dated 11/4/16 was lodged with Renault customer care. To surprise we received a call from Mr. Gaurav Negi, Renault India on 13/4/16 followed by letter from Ms. Neetu Chawla, Renault India informing us that the car technology is tamper proof. We doused the fire ourself, without informing Delhi Fire Brigade & Delhi Police and disconnected battery terminal to prevent further burning due to short circuit & petrol tank catching fire We are elderly senior citizen couple living in Delhi, with both sons staying in Germany. We are very worried to see the fire in engine. We fear risk to our life. We purchased this car from our savings. Renault India is deliberately denying their faulty design as reason for fire in engine. The car has run less than 2000 km in five months. The Renault Kwid has 2 years warranty against manufacturing defects as per the clause 2 of Terms and Conditions of KWID Vehicle WarrantY They have kept our car at their workshop at Rama Road, Delhi since early morning 11/4/16 with no action taken to provide us alternate car for usage till time new car is provided to us as replacement. Please take action against Renault India and direct them to stop sales of their defective designed car KWID in market, till period the defect is removed and they declare their KWID is safe to drive, in Indian condition. I request you to direct Delhi Fire Brigade and Delhi Police to take suo motto cognizance of fire in Renault Kwid Car engine and take action to stop sales of KWID in Indian market. Sincerely, Rajesh Ghai B6/70 sector 8, Rohini, Delhi-110085 9810434027 : 01147541414 .

author: wongawonga1000
comment_text: The smug attitude shown by some of the team members was totally uncalled for. Most people who start driving these cars have been racing from a very young age and so have time to build the skill level required to handle a high performance vehicle. Richard is a TV show host who's probably never done any serious racing in his life - especially at that level. It's little wonder then that he had trouble driving the cars and was constantly stalling them. Even Lewis Hamilton, who appeared immediately after this segment, said that those cars were very difficult to drive. In this situation therefore, a little understanding wouldn't have gone astray - particularly given the steep learning curve Richard was faced with.

author: Wayne Rhodes
comment_text: With nothing more than 93 octane and pulled the rubber seal out of the intake track so she gets fresh outside air and a 15 0z. bottle of Lucas octane booster, shifting without lifting, she gets to 60 in just a tick over 6 seconds in sport mod, and it really made this little light weight come alive took out the full size spare tire 37 pounds of weight savings I carry an electric air pump and a can of fix-a-flat with me at all times. If I did not have to shift to third it would get to 60 in just under 6 seconds I am sure of it. It now has almost 4000 miles on its clock and two oil changes already one at 500 miles and the other at 2000 miles. comment_text: Well.. it is too hard for me choice one from them.... Therefore, i brought both the ST and RS 220, haha. On top of that, you wont be feeling any turbo lag on the fiesta at all. Unlike the RS 220, there is a window that you have to wait for the boost to come around 1k rpm to 2k rpm. This is really the biggest different.   However, the RS is just quicker. (I put MP215 to mine as well), it gives you the stability in high speed and also in the corner which the Fiesta can't offer. author: anthony perkins
comment_text: The LR Discovery Series II was never tested for safety by EURONCAP and was merely a facelift and cosmetic changes to the original LR Discovery Series I.   The old design was made before safety was even thought of and wouldn't keep anyone safe in a collision.  All the Disco I and Disco II got were driver airbags at first followed by twin driver / passenger airbags as standard but apart from this no real changes to the design for safety in a collision.  The Renault Espace is the far safer place to be and people would be far less injured in it, than the Discovery.

author: Paolo Ciarpaglini
comment_text: "X Roberto ... Oggi ci sono i bimbiminchia come li chiami tu, ai nostri tempi c'erano i bimbipiloti. Insomma i tempi sono mutati e a nassuno interessa piu' affiancarsi al semaforo e ... via. Il problema e' almeno per me che faccio molta fatica ad abituarmi a una realta' mutata tutta a favore di loro, e mi mancano tanto, da morire le serate dei fine settimana in cui mi sentivo il re del mondo. Cio' che resta sono ricordi di un tempo che sembra impossibile essere esistito, che faceva coppia perfetta con i ""nativi"", i veri e unici abitanti di quelle sere. Mi vestivo scendevo e al momento di accenderla iniziava una sorta di danza e istinto tribale, fatto di rumori e suoni che esprimevano piccoli sogni divenuti reali. Erano tempi infinitamente piu' a misura d'uomo, di esseri umani che trascorsa l'infanzia in canottiera bianca e appena uscita dalla disco '80, si affacciava verso l'ultimo decennio sulle note di ""Cosa restera'"" di Raf e la PX elaborata ancora in garage. Con l'avvento dei duemila e' iniziata una mutazione genetica divenuta poi sempre piu' frenetica, folle, un no sense mentre i capelli bianchi aumentavano e iniziavi (parlo per me) a sentirti come un orologio fuori sincronia. Continuo ad osservare tutto cio' e ancora non mi capacito di cosa e' accaduto, ai prati dove giocavamo e a regole non scritte che facevano di quei tempi qualcosa di molto migliore, di semplice, di indimenticabile. Salutai la mia Uno prima serie nel '98 e fu come staccarmi qualcosa che sapevo non avrei mai piu' avuto. Ma .. The show must go on e il destino ha voluto che due anni fa acquistassi una Punto 2^ serie hgt nera tenuta benissimo che mi aiuta a sentirmi meno sperduto in mezzo a tutte queste auto tutte uguali computerizzate, avanzate ma che non sanno neppure di acqua calda. Qualcuno mi guarda ogni tanto quasi fossi un marziano, ma faccio finta di niente. Dimenticavo ""la bara"", soli 149 cv alla ruota con turbina originale e pressione di sicurezza ad 1 bar, piu' un profondo lavoro che mi costo' 9 milioni e ottocento mila lire. Non capisco il volerne 220 poiche' ingestibili e fatti per durare appena il tempo della spesa. Non so se hai notato ma fumano entrambe in modo poco incoraggiante. E poi 245 di tachimetro erano piu' che sufficenti. Come i miei 30 anni trascorsi ormai da un pezzo, anzi un era. Ma .. e' la vita."

author: KerberosRS
comment_text: "Oggi ho 45 anni e io avevo una Fiesta Turbo 133cv ( quella con le strisce verdi per chi si ricorda), diretta concorrente di questi mostri. Sebbene molti dicono lo fosse anche la mia per me queste auto non erano delle bare la mia ce l'ho avuta per 5 anni e no ho mai fatto un graffio ( come nei restanti anni di guida d'altronde).... per√≤ se posso dire la mia esperienza devo ammettere che il sistema di frenata di queste auto era assolutamente inadeguato... il fatto di non avere un ABS portava all inevitabile blocco dei pneumatici anteriori nelle frenate di emergenza ed era facile "" andare dritto""..io ricordo che per ovviare il problema facevo manualmente l'effetto dell'ABS prima spingendo con decisione e appena avvertivo il blocco dei pneumatici saltellando con decisione con la pianta del piede sul freno. Comunque questi motori erano davvero pazzeschi a volte la turbina dava dei contraccolpi tali che si facevano veri e propri salti sui sedili ( per fortuna avevo dei fantastici RECARO). Ricordo che quando l'ho demolita nel 2002 piansi per una mezz'ora buona come se fosse morta una persona a me cara....ancora oggi ogni tanto vado a cercare le vecchie foto ( su carta stampata e poi digitalizzate) fatte con lei..ricordi.. di gioie... dolori ...vacanze....spensieratezza..follia ... amiche e vecchi amici."

author: aditya giri
comment_text: I purchased Renault Kwid Rxt model in March 2017 from Avia Auto Services Patpadganj branch. Since then in less than a year I have taken my car to service station for over 10 times for various issues.  Issue No. 1 When I purchased the car I was fraudulently given a Comprehensive Insurance Policy instead of a Zero Dep. Policy. Which incurred me losses every time I claimed my insurance.  Issue No.2 There is only one reverse light in the car on the left side and no light is provided at the right side of vehicle which creates problem whenever I try to reverse my car.  Issue No. 3 They claim that car gives an average of 25kmpl. Which I totally false claim and nowhere near 25 kmpl you can expect in a city like Delhi.  Issue No. 4 Back in July 2017 when monsoon begun, my car got flooded with rain water and my laptop and documents were destroyed.   Issue No.5 The body is made of plastic and is so is the base of engine. The engine due to a small stone got damaged and oil chambers had to change. Which costed me 7500 approx. The service department asked me to get an engine protection for Rs 1800/- which the Renault was supposed to install before selling the vehicle.  Issue 6 Since I was not holding a zero dep policy in the first year I faced great difficulty in purchasing a zero dep this year. The Renault Team is so unprofessional that they don't even reply to my mails and complaints.   If you are planning to buy Renault car kindly have a review from it's prior users and watch YouTube videos regarding issues with Renault car. I have been duped but I want to beware other innocent buyers from buying this piece of plastic.   If you are also suffering from same kindly contact me at: giriaditya5@yahoo.co.in  Since I am planning to move to consumer court soon for this harassment, cheating & fraud.

author: Don Jonson
comment_text: Nice... but, I'll still rather have my 1976 lincoln town car. 7.8 liter engine (460) 4 barrel carb. It had the trailer pulling package so that included 4 wheel disc brakes, a 3 core radiator, and posi-traction rear end. It weighed, about 5500 lbs. The hood itself is like 6 feet long. LOTS of room for impact and lots of material to absorb a crash.  Yeah, so it got 9 mpg. It was comfy, good in the winter (you would be surprised how good because of the posi and the weight), and safe.   Shit, I could fit that whole Renault in my hood.   I was rear-ended in it back in 1984 by some jerk in a Chevy Monza.  He hit me doing about 25 mph. My big heavy chrome bumper was bent a little but no damage to the trunk.  meanwhile, his 2 front quarter panels were pushed over his doors. . he cold not open his door and had to crawl out the window. Wheels bent, front glass broken and every fluid in the car was leaking out the bottom. His car was un-driveable.  My friends and I felt a small BUMP when he hit us.   His car was towed and totaled. I drove away and for $900 my car was repaired.

author: Ishan Ghai
comment_text: Renault KWID caught Fire  Renault India for supplying me faulty vehicle Renault Kwid RXT model purchased on 26/10/15 with no extra fittings/ accessories except mud flaps.After my first summer trip to faridabad, came back home around 5pm, thereafter it was a nightmare for us, as around 12 mid night, we woked up by alarms from neighbours of fire in our car. We poured water to extinguish the fire. On inspection of car we observed the engine compartment fully melted down due to internal wiring / faulty design, in parked conditions. We came to know of damage, only when car catched fire around 12 mid night. We thank our stars, that this top end model didn't catches fire, when we were driving the car. Renault India cheated on us, by introducing unsafe car in India. A Complaint was lodged with Renault at 1 AM after the incidence. In morning, on Complaint to Renault 24 hour help line, my car was picked up and inspected. The car engine was fully gutted, even tyres were got affected. I was told we would be given a new car as replacement as car has been damaged due to fault in design /wiring. All Renault staff asked us many questions and even visited the site of incidence. A Complaint no. 4-01783350 dated 11/4/16 was lodged with Renault customer care. To surprise we received a call from Mr. Gaurav Negi, Renault India on 13/4/16 followed by letter from Ms. Neetu Chawla, Renault India informing us that the car technology is tamper proof. We doused the fire ourself, without informing Delhi Fire Brigade & Delhi Police and disconnected battery terminal to prevent further burning due to short circuit & petrol tank catching fire We are elderly senior citizen couple living in Delhi, with both sons staying in Germany. We are very worried to see the fire in engine. We fear risk to our life. We purchased this car from our savings. Renault India is deliberately denying their faulty design as reason for fire in engine. The car has run less than 2000 km in five months. The Renault Kwid has 2 years warranty against manufacturing defects as per the clause 2 of Terms and Conditions of KWID Vehicle WarrantY They have kept our car at their workshop at Rama Road, Delhi since early morning 11/4/16 with no action taken to provide us alternate car for usage till time new car is provided to us as replacement. Please take action against Renault India and direct them to stop sales of their defective designed car KWID in market, till period the defect is removed and they declare their KWID is safe to drive, in Indian condition. I request you to direct Delhi Fire Brigade and Delhi Police to take suo motto cognizance of fire in Renault Kwid Car engine and take action to stop sales of KWID in Indian market. Sincerely, Rajesh Ghai B6/70 sector 8, Rohini, Delhi-110085 9810434027 : 01147541414 .

comment_text: "Pour ceux qui se demandent ce que signifie le nom ""Mistral Gagnant"", voici une petite explication: Mistral Gagnant"" √©tait le nom d'une poudre vendue dans un sachet herm√©tique dans lequel on pouvait verser de l'eau, et cela faisait un soda orange ou citron. Et il s'appelait ""Gagnant"", parce qu'en retournant le sachet, on pouvait lire dans certains cas la mention ""Gagnant"", ce qui permettait d'en avoir un gratuit en rapportant le papier au marchand.  Renaud, trente ans plus tard, prom√®ne sa fillette de 3 ou 4 ans, et repense du coup √† son enfance, alors il veut lui faire d√©couvrir les bonbons qu'il aimait √©tant enfant: Les caramels √† un franc(ancien franc des ann√©es 50), les Coco Bohair, vendus dans une petite poche m√©tallique avec laquelle on se coupait la langue les jours de maladresse, et les Mistral Gagnant: En promenant sa fille, Renaud se rend compte que tous ces bonbons ont disparu: Il voudrait les lui faire d√©couvrir, on devine qu'il a cherch√© dans les magasins, mais les commer√ßants lui expliquent ce ""√ßa ne se fait plus""... D'o√π la fin: ""Le temps est assassin et emporte avec lui les rires des enfants... et les Mistral Gagnant"". Renaud, d√©sabus√©, a perdu son rire d'enfant, et il ne retrouvera plus les saveurs de son enfance, mais il veut malgr√© tout continuer √† aimer la vie. C'est une histoire tr√®s simple, mais sublime, parfaitement racont√©e, sur une musique magique qui exhale toute la puret√© de l'enfance. S'il n'y avait qu'un disque de chansons pour le monde entier, ""Mistral Gagnant"" y aurait s√ªrement sa place."

author: wongawonga1000
comment_text: The smug attitude shown by some of the team members was totally uncalled for. Most people who start driving these cars have been racing from a very young age and so have time to build the skill level required to handle a high performance vehicle. Richard is a TV show host who's probably never done any serious racing in his life - especially at that level. It's little wonder then that he had trouble driving the cars and was constantly stalling them. Even Lewis Hamilton, who appeared immediately after this segment, said that those cars were very difficult to drive. In this situation therefore, a little understanding wouldn't have gone astray - particularly given the steep learning curve Richard was faced with.

author: tin long yuen
comment_text: Well.. it is too hard for me choice one from them.... Therefore, i brought both the ST and RS 220, haha. But i have to said that the Fiesta is simply much more fun to drive which the RS can't give you on the street. The sharpness and responsiveness of the Fiesta is amazing. On top of that, you wont be feeling any turbo lag on the fiesta at all. Unlike the RS 220, there is a window that you have to wait for the boost to come around 1k rpm to 2k rpm. This is really the biggest different.   However, the RS is just quicker. (I put MP215 to mine as well), it gives you the stability in high speed and also in the corner which the Fiesta can't offer. (i put F1A3 in Fiesta and PSS in RS).

author: anthony perkins
comment_text: The LR Discovery Series II was never tested for safety by EURONCAP and was merely a facelift and cosmetic changes to the original LR Discovery Series I.   The old design was made before safety was even thought of and wouldn't keep anyone safe in a collision.  All the Disco I and Disco II got were driver airbags at first followed by twin driver / passenger airbags as standard but apart from this no real changes to the design for safety in a collision.  The Renault Espace is the far safer place to be and people would be far less injured in it, than the Discovery.

comment_text: "There are ""no chase"" policies in many places for a reason. Chasing this motorcycle is only increasing the threat to people's lives. He crashes that motorcycle, he dies. Police crash that car and the likelihood of someone else dying goes up exponentially. Especially when the bike has something to run from now, pushing his speed from 230km/hr to 299+km/hr. It's just not worth chasing speeders that are going that fast unless they have committed some kind of violent crime before running at that speed. The likelyhood of a negative outcome is very high when a hypercar is chasing a sportbike down the road at 300km/hr in a non closed environment. The very premise of this video is rather unintelligent."

Insomma i tempi sono mutati e a nassuno interessa piu' affiancarsi al semaforo e ... via. Il problema e' almeno per me che faccio molta fatica ad abituarmi a una realta' mutata tutta a favore di loro, e mi mancano tanto, da morire le serate dei fine settimana in cui mi sentivo il re del mondo. Cio' che resta sono ricordi di un tempo che sembra impossibile essere esistito, che faceva coppia perfetta con i ""nativi"", i veri e unici abitanti di quelle sere. Mi vestivo scendevo e al momento di accenderla iniziava una sorta di danza e istinto tribale, fatto di rumori e suoni che esprimevano piccoli sogni divenuti reali. Erano tempi infinitamente piu' a misura d'uomo, di esseri umani che trascorsa l'infanzia in canottiera bianca e appena uscita dalla disco '80, si affacciava verso l'ultimo decennio sulle note di ""Cosa restera'"" di Raf e la PX elaborata ancora in garage. Con l'avvento dei duemila e' iniziata una mutazione genetica divenuta poi sempre piu' frenetica, folle, un no sense mentre i capelli bianchi aumentavano e iniziavi (parlo per me) a sentirti come un orologio fuori sincronia. Continuo ad osservare tutto cio' e ancora non mi capacito di cosa e' accaduto, ai prati dove giocavamo e a regole non scritte che facevano di quei tempi qualcosa di molto migliore, di semplice, di indimenticabile. Salutai la mia Uno prima serie nel '98 e fu come staccarmi qualcosa che sapevo non avrei mai piu' avuto. Ma .. The show must go on e il destino ha voluto che due anni fa acquistassi una Punto 2^ serie hgt nera tenuta benissimo che mi aiuta a sentirmi meno sperduto in mezzo a tutte queste auto tutte uguali computerizzate, avanzate ma che non sanno neppure di acqua calda. Qualcuno mi guarda ogni tanto quasi fossi un marziano, ma faccio finta di niente. Dimenticavo ""la bara"", soli 149 cv alla ruota con turbina originale e pressione di sicurezza ad 1 bar, piu' un profondo lavoro che mi costo' 9 milioni e ottocento mila lire. Non capisco il volerne 220 poiche' ingestibili e fatti per durare appena il tempo della spesa. Non so se hai notato ma fumano entrambe in modo poco incoraggiante. E poi 245 di tachimetro erano piu' che sufficenti. Come i miei 30 anni trascorsi ormai da un pezzo, anzi un era. Ma .. e' la vita."

comment_text: "Oggi ho 45 anni e io avevo una Fiesta Turbo 133cv ( quella con le strisce verdi per chi si ricorda), diretta concorrente di questi mostri. Sebbene molti dicono lo fosse anche la mia per me queste auto non erano delle bare la mia ce l'ho avuta per 5 anni e no ho mai fatto un graffio ( come nei restanti anni di guida d'altronde).... per√≤ se posso dire la mia esperienza devo ammettere che il sistema di frenata di queste auto era assolutamente inadeguato... il fatto di non avere un ABS portava all inevitabile blocco dei pneumatici anteriori nelle frenate di emergenza ed era facile "" andare dritto""..io ricordo che per ovviare il problema facevo manualmente l'effetto dell'ABS prima spingendo con decisione e appena avvertivo il blocco dei pneumatici saltellando con decisione con la pianta del piede sul freno. Comunque questi motori erano davvero pazzeschi a volte la turbina dava dei contraccolpi tali che si facevano veri e propri salti sui sedili ( per fortuna avevo dei fantastici RECARO). Ricordo che quando l'ho demolita nel 2002 piansi per una mezz'ora buona come se fosse morta una persona a me cara....ancora oggi ogni tanto vado a cercare le vecchie foto ( su carta stampata e poi digitalizzate) fatte con lei..ricordi.. di gioie... dolori ...vacanze....spensieratezza..follia ... amiche e vecchi amici."

author: aditya giri
comment_text: I purchased Renault Kwid Rxt model in March 2017 from Avia Auto Services Patpadganj branch. Since then in less than a year I have taken my car to service station for over 10 times for various issues.  Issue No. 1 When I purchased the car I was fraudulently given a Comprehensive Insurance Policy instead of a Zero Dep. Policy. Which incurred me losses every time I claimed my insurance.  Issue No.2 There is only one reverse light in the car on the left side and no light is provided at the right side of vehicle which creates problem whenever I try to reverse my car.  Issue No. 3 They claim that car gives an average of 25kmpl. Which I totally false claim and nowhere near 25 kmpl you can expect in a city like Delhi.  Issue No. 4 Back in July 2017 when monsoon begun, my car got flooded with rain water and my laptop and documents were destroyed.   Issue No.5 The body is made of plastic and is so is the base of engine. The engine due to a small stone got damaged and oil chambers had to change. Which costed me 7500 approx. The service department asked me to get an engine protection for Rs 1800/- which the Renault was supposed to install before selling the vehicle.  Issue 6 Since I was not holding a zero dep policy in the first year I faced great difficulty in purchasing a zero dep this year. The Renault Team is so unprofessional that they don't even reply to my mails and complaints.   If you are planning to buy Renault car kindly have a review from it's prior users and watch YouTube videos regarding issues with Renault car. I have been duped but I want to beware other innocent buyers from buying this piece of plastic.   If you are also suffering from same kindly contact me at: giriaditya5@yahoo.co.in  Since I am planning to move to consumer court soon for this harassment, cheating & fraud.

author: Don Jonson
comment_text: Nice... but, I'll still rather have my 1976 lincoln town car. 7.8 liter engine (460) 4 barrel carb. It had the trailer pulling package so that included 4 wheel disc brakes, a 3 core radiator, and posi-traction rear end. It weighed, about 5500 lbs. The hood itself is like 6 feet long. LOTS of room for impact and lots of material to absorb a crash.  Yeah, so it got 9 mpg. It was comfy, good in the winter (you would be surprised how good because of the posi and the weight), and safe.   Shit, I could fit that whole Renault in my hood.   I was rear-ended in it back in 1984 by some jerk in a Chevy Monza.  He hit me doing about 25 mph. My big heavy chrome bumper was bent a little but no damage to the trunk.  meanwhile, his 2 front quarter panels were pushed over his doors. . he cold not open his door and had to crawl out the window. Wheels bent, front glass broken and every fluid in the car was leaking out the bottom. His car was un-driveable.  My friends and I felt a small BUMP when he hit us.   His car was towed and totaled. I drove away and for $900 my car was repaired.

author: Ishan Ghai
comment_text: Renault KWID caught Fire  Renault India for supplying me faulty vehicle Renault Kwid RXT model purchased on 26/10/15 with no extra fittings/ accessories except mud flaps.After my first summer trip to faridabad, came back home around 5pm, thereafter it was a nightmare for us, as around 12 mid night, we woked up by alarms from neighbours of fire in our car. We poured water to extinguish the fire. On inspection of car we observed the engine compartment fully melted down due to internal wiring / faulty design, in parked conditions. We came to know of damage, only when car catched fire around 12 mid night. We thank our stars, that this top end model didn't catches fire, when we were driving the car. Renault India cheated on us, by introducing unsafe car in India. A Complaint was lodged with Renault at 1 AM after the incidence. In morning, on Complaint to Renault 24 hour help line, my car was picked up and inspected. The car engine was fully gutted, even tyres were got affected. I was told we would be given a new car as replacement as car has been damaged due to fault in design /wiring. All Renault staff asked us many questions and even visited the site of incidence. A Complaint no. 4-01783350 dated 11/4/16 was lodged with Renault customer care. To surprise we received a call from Mr. Gaurav Negi, Renault India on 13/4/16 followed by letter from Ms. Neetu Chawla, Renault India informing us that the car technology is tamper proof. We doused the fire ourself, without informing Delhi Fire Brigade & Delhi Police and disconnected battery terminal to prevent further burning due to short circuit & petrol tank catching fire We are elderly senior citizen couple living in Delhi, with both sons staying in Germany. We are very worried to see the fire in engine. We fear risk to our life. We purchased this car from our savings. Renault India is deliberately denying their faulty design as reason for fire in engine. The car has run less than 2000 km in five months. The Renault Kwid has 2 years warranty against manufacturing defects as per the clause 2 of Terms and Conditions of KWID Vehicle WarrantY They have kept our car at their workshop at Rama Road, Delhi since early morning 11/4/16 with no action taken to provide us alternate car for usage till time new car is provided to us as replacement. Please take action against Renault India and direct them to stop sales of their defective designed car KWID in market, till period the defect is removed and they declare their KWID is safe to drive, in Indian condition. I request you to direct Delhi Fire Brigade and Delhi Police to take suo motto cognizance of fire in Renault Kwid Car engine and take action to stop sales of KWID in Indian market. Sincerely, Rajesh Ghai B6/70 sector 8, Rohini, Delhi-110085 9810434027 : 01147541414 .
